full_text:
Wow... wild!  While I&#39;m testing in preparation to shoot the video, 
having all 3 modified radios sweeping the fm band and processing all 
that &quot;raw audio&quot; through the mixture and into the computer sure makes 
for some wild noise.  It does assure that you&#39;re receiving from three 
different points on the FM band at any given moment since each radio 
is sweeping at its own pace and place on that band! But you&#39;re 
hearing the raw audio from all three at the same time.  Now I&#39;ll have 
to mix and match bands to see what that produces.
Note: I did find out I need a different microphone, one that is a 
better match for the mixer.
Stay tuned...

Mike

