&gt; TV, from my 3 modified RS digital radios.)
&gt; 
&gt; Those 3 sources of &quot;raw&quot; audio will be fed into a mixer, along with 
a 
&gt; microphone into the mixer.  The output will be fed into a laptop 
&gt; running an audio capture program capable of level trigger recording.
&gt; 
&gt; A person could start a session, ask a question, and after the 
&gt; question set the program to listen to the sources of raw audio for 
a 
&gt; set amount of time after the question is asked. The program is 
&gt; adjustable to allow for time-frame deviation after the microphone 
&gt; level goes to a low peak.
&gt; 
&gt; This all gets recorded (session questions and entities answers) 
into 
&gt; a .wav file which could be given to a person after the session is 
&gt; finished. The session could be as long as you like.
&gt; 
&gt; The .wav file could then be burned onto a CD right after the 
session 
&gt; is done.  The person could walk away from that session with the 
&gt; entire session on the CD for their record and to listen to at their 
&gt; leisure.
&gt; 
&gt; The input levels, trigger level, and time frame to allow an answer 
&gt; are all set by the person running the session.  Its all automated 
&gt; after the initial setup.  And it&#39;s all portable, no AC plug in 
&gt; needed. Batteries run everything!
&gt; 
&gt; Kinda cool I think!
&gt; 
&gt; Anyway, I&#39;ll post that video of my complete setup and a mock 
session 
&gt; this week sometime.  This way people can get an idea of how they 
can 
&gt; use the modified radios.
&gt; 
&gt; Take care...
&gt; 
&gt; - Mike
